    "description": "Working with explosives to blow stuff up. This skill also covers&nbsp;<span style=\"color: var(--s2d6-light-color); font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit;\">defusing said explosives before they blow up.</span><div>• Set up an explosive charge: roll Demolitions (EDU) 6+, or more for complex&nbsp;<span style=\"color: var(--s2d6-light-color); font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit;\">jobs, such as setting a directional shaped charge explosive.</span></div><div>• Defuse an explosive charge: this could be as simple as pressing a single&nbsp;<span style=\"color: var(--s2d6-light-color); font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit;\">button on a remote control, if the bomb was set by the same character. In&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: var(--s2d6-light-color); font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit;\">most cases, roll Demolitions (EDU) 8+ to defuse explosives set by someone&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: var(--s2d6-light-color); font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit;\">else, or more if it was deliberately made to be tricky to work with (i.e. a bomb&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: var(--s2d6-light-color); font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit;\">custom built by a terrorist trying to cause a disaster could be harder than an&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: var(--s2d6-light-color); font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit;\">off-the-shelf equipment activated by regular instructions).</span></div>",
